          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Even though his par=
tnership group contained several I.R.R.-hungry masters of the universe, Gro=
usbeck said they were willing to think differently about owning the Celtics=
=2E And there was never a second cap=
ital call. =E2=80=9CEvery single person c=
ame in and thought about it as the emotional satisfaction of being part of =
something bigger than ourselves,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CWe made that cl=
ear to everybody. I said, =E2=80=98We=E2=80=99re probably overpaying. We=E2=
=80=99re going to be paid in enjoyment,=E2=80=99 was my phrase at the time.=
 =E2=80=98This is the last Boston team I think that=E2=80=99s going to sell=
 in our lifetimes. And imagine if we win? I think we can be competitive and=
 not go totally broke. If there=E2=80=99s ever any extra money lying around=
, we=E2=80=99re going to put it into the team and try to make the team bett=
er. Having said that, if there=E2=80=99s ever <i>really</i> extra money aro=
und, we=E2=80=99ll
all share it out equally.=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D <br/><br/>There were no puts. T=
here were no hurdle rates. There was no preferred stock. =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=
=99re all in it, really together,=E2=80=9D he told his new partners. =E2=80=
=9CEverybody came in for love. They=E2=80=99re all great business people, b=
ut they came in for love and passion, and then it has worked out better tha=
n we even thought.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Grousbeck and his partners completed t=
he purchase on New Year=E2=80=99s Eve, 2002. They retained the legendary <b=
>Red Auerbach</b>=E2=80=94who had been reappointed team president in late 2=
001=E2=80=94as a link to the once-great Celtics teams of past eras; hired <=
b>Danny Ainge</b> as G.M. and <b>Doc Rivers</b> as coach; and masterminded =
the trades that landed <b>Kevin Garnett </b>and <b>Ray Allen </b>to play be=
side <b>Paul Pierce </b>in his prime=E2=80=94the first real <i>Big Three </=
i>concept of the modern era. In 2008, of course, that team brought the Larr=
y O=E2=80=99Brien Trophy back to Boston for the first time since 1986. Then=
 in June, behind a
talented young core led by <b>Jason Tatum</b> and <b>Jaylen Brown</b>, <b>J=
oe Mazzulla</b> won the NBA title in his only second season, one of the you=
ngest coaches to ever win a championship. =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99ve had great =
people running the basketball side and great players and great fans,=E2=80=
=9D Grousbeck said. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s all been a really amazing ride.=
=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Ainslie wanted to know what advice Grousbeck had for oth=
er current or aspiring team owners. Grousbeck is also a part owner of Cinco=
ro Tequila, along with his wife and several other NBA team owners, includin=
g <b>Michael Jordan</b>, <b>Jeanie Buss</b>, and <b>Wes Edens</b>. =E2=80=
=9CThey=E2=80=99re not asking me for advice, but we all share insights,=E2=
=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CLet=E2=80=99s put it this way: Wes would rather di=
e than ask me for advice. That=E2=80=99s how good he is.=E2=80=9D First, he=
 said, you can=E2=80=99t run a team to maximize profits. =E2=80=9CThe fans =
will figure it out,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CPlayers will figure it out. =
You shouldn=E2=80=99t do it. You should be lucky
enough to be able to run these for love, and then you probably will not go =
broke.=E2=80=9D <br/><br/>Grousbeck said he was probably the =E2=80=9Cleast=
 well-capitalized owner=E2=80=9D in the NBA, =E2=80=9Cbut we=E2=80=99ve bee=
n successful because we put the money into the team. We=E2=80=99re not bett=
er than anybody else.=E2=80=9D So long as the owners have a passion for the=
 team, =E2=80=9Ceverything will work out fine, but not the other way around=
=2E=E2=80=9D If you are trying to decide b=
etween owning a sports team or owni=
ng Nvidia, he joked, =E2=80=9Cstick to the stock market,=E2=80=9D he said.<=
br/><br/>Finally, he showed off to the Zoom audience the massive 2024 champ=
ionship ring that the team=E2=80=99s owners and players received. The top o=
f the ring comes off to display a miniature championship banner and piece o=
f the Celtics parquet floor. <br/><br/>Now, Grousbeck <i>et al</i>. are all=
 just waiting for the team to be sold. And, no, he said, he doesn=E2=80=99t=
 have a number in mind, assuming there=E2=80=99s someone out there who has =
the guts to ask
him.<br/></td>
